<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8023> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8023" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. Pl. 44. In MRR 2.324, refer also to Syme, JRS 51, 1961, 23-24-RP 2.518-519; Wiseman, NM 233, no. 203.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 8023 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5976> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5976" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He proposed the measure which deprived Caesetius and Marullus of their tribunician powers (see above; Liv. Per. 116; Nic. Dam. Vit. Caes. 20.9, FGrH 2A.405; 22.1, ibid. 406; App. BC 2.108; Dio 44.10.3; 46.49.2; Obseq. 70), and it was said had already drawn up a bill at Caesar's wish empowering Caesar to marry such and so many wives as he wished (Suet. Iul. 52.3; Dio 44.7.3). He was killed by the crowd after Caesar's funeral by mistake for the Praetor Cinna (Val. Max. 9.9.1; Suet. Iul. 85; Plut. Caes. 68.2; Brut. 20.5-6; App. BC 2.147; Dio 44.50.4, and 52.2; 45.6.3; 46.49.2; 47.11.3; Obseq. 70; Zonar. 10.12). On his identification with the poet Cinna, see Plut. Brut. 20.5; Schwabe, Philologus 47 (1889) 169f., and against it, Deutsch, CJ 20 (1925) 326ff." ;
	dprr:hasID 5976 .
